  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dba\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd6 \u0d9a\u0dad\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u2018\u2018\u0db4\u0dab\u2018\u2018 \u0d87\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dad\u0dd1\u0d9c\u0dca\u0d9c\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A \"living\" gift from a loved one on the plane",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Kalutara police reports that a woman who was close to her left to take care of her two-year-old child on a flight from Saudi Arabia ran away.",
        "S. resident of Kalutara South, Bodhiiwatta area. According to a complaint made by Shanta Appuhami, investigations have been started.",
        "The police have stated that Kataka, who had worked in Saudi Arabia for about 11 years, was coming from the plane with a 2-year-old boy, was recognized on the plane, and at the Katunayake airport, she was told that she also wanted to go to Kalutara, so she and the child were picked up in the same taxi that she came from, the police said. said",
        "The police said that the complaint has recorded that while arriving in Kalutara city, the child said that he was bringing a bottle of soft drink and got out of the vehicle and did not return.",
        "Kalutara South Headquarters Police Inspector Mr. Suneth Shanta is conducting investigations under the leadership of Police Inspector Nuwanti, Child and Women's Bureau of Kalutara South Police Station."
      ],
